article.description: — Tosan Evbuomwan had a career-high 27 points, including the game-winning basket with 3.4 seconds left, as Princeton narrowly beat Drexel 81-79 in overtime on Saturday.
article.headline: Evbuomwan lifts Princeton over Drexel 81-79 in OT
article.linkText: Evbuomwan lifts Princeton over Drexel 81-79 in OT
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- — Tosan Evbuomwan had a career-high 27 points, including the game-winning basket with 3.4 seconds left, as Princeton narrowly beat Drexel 81-79 in overtime on Saturday. Ryan Langborg had 17 points and blocked a potential game winner at the end of regulation for Princeton (6-3), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Jaelin Llewellyn added 15 points. Ethan Wright had 10 points and eight rebounds. Camren Wynter had 18 points for the Dragons (4-4). Xavier Bell added 17 points. James Butler had 14 points and 12 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
